  "body": "Hi there,\r\n\r\nI've got an issue with testing on the simulated backend.\r\nFor instance if build and run following example (https://github.com/miguelmota/ethereum-development-with-go-book/blob/master/code/client_simulated.go) it falls  with following error:\r\n\r\n`invalid transaction: invalid transaction v, r, s values`\r\n\r\n#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: `1.9.0-unstable`\r\nOS & Version: OSX\r\nCommit hash : (if `develop`)\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\n\r\nSent ETH to an address\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\n\r\n`invalid transaction: invalid transaction v, r, s values`\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\n\r\nRun the example above\r\n\r\n#### Backtrace\r\n\r\n````\r\npanic: invalid transaction: invalid transaction v, r, s values\r\n\r\ngoroutine 1 [running]:\r\ngithub.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/accounts/abi/bind/backends.(*SimulatedBackend).SendTransaction(0xc00002e680, 0x4628d80, 0xc0000240a8, 0xc0000da630, 0x0, 0x0)\r\n\t/Users/ssi/go/src/github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/accounts/abi/bind/backends/simulated.go:321 +0x611\r\nmain.main()\r\n\t/Users/ssi/cryptoda_token/sbc.go:60 +0x5c8\r\nexit status 2\r\n````\r\n`sbc.go` is the script above",
