    "body": "@ssi91 So, the issue was that the simulated backend had the homestead signature scheme hard coded instead of EIP155 (the chainID one). Now I fixed that. It should still accept Homestead signatures (with a nil chain ID), but also non-nil chain IDs. Note, you still need to use 1337 for the ID (we forcefully use something that's incompatible with mainnet to avoid accidents).",
